Chambers and Partner 2017


    Corporate/Commercial: East Coast: Beijing (PRC Firms) (Band 1);


    Capital Markets: Domestic Issuances (Band 3);



      Capital Markets: Hong Kong and Overseas Issuances (Band 3)

I was an assistant teacher in the experiential learning program run for year nine students (14-15 years of age) in Nanjing. 
My responsibilities included:
- pastoral care;
-general administration; 
-teaching;
-supervising student activities; and 
-basic first aid.

I specialise in providing tax advisory and compliance services in relation to the income tax affairs of foreign and Australian companies. My sectors of expertise include energy and natural resources, infrastructure, consumer and industrial markets.

My key responsibilities include:

- Prepare and draft advice papers on various Australian and international income tax issues including structuring options for inbound and outbound investors, business acquisitions and restructures;
- Review and prepare income tax returns of consolidated corporate groups, standalone companies, trusts and partnerships;
- Conduct tax provision reviews as well as high level review of deferred tax calculations;
- Assist with dealings/disputes with the Australian Taxation Office;
- Direct day to day advisory of clients; and
- Facilitate and organise training sessions as well as prepare case summaries and decision impact reports for team development.

Assisting clients take advantage of Australian R&D Tax Incentives and grants with:


    - the preparation of their R&D plans and costings for submission in their tax returns;



      - the preparation of grants submissions
